<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>38<percent/> of 118</li> 
<li>87<percent/> of 70</li> 
<li>5<percent/> of 2853</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>C: 5<percent/> of 2853</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{87}\%\cdot{70}={60.9}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{38}\%\cdot{118}={44.84}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{5}\%\cdot{2853}={142.65}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 5<percent/> of 2853 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

